# (''Australian'') A [[pal]], [[buddy]], [[mate]]. Synonymous with [[digger]]. Australian goldfields produced a lot of clay-based [[spoil]] as the pits were dug. This was often used as building material, making unformed (usually red) mud [[cob]] huts.  It is proposed ''without proof'' that this made a [[digger]] a "cobber". 
